-1765072823.text: "With hypofractionated radiotherapy regimen in mind, it was remarkable that DLL3, a divergent Notch ligand family member that does not activate Notch signaling in adjacent cells but inhibits Notch receptors when expressed in the same cell [XREF_BIBR], was consistently induced after higher doses of 6 and 8 Gy, suggesting that signaling relevant for breast cancer stem cells at these large fractions differs from signaling seen after conventional fractions of 2 Gy."
